@sammmmurai, if you're putting it on an external HDD and using Wii Backup Manager (same as me) why bother converting it into an ISO?  WBM by default converts anything not already in wbfs into it to save space on your HDD.  With this game for example wbfs format saves you 0.93GB by removing dummy files, update partition, etc.

@kupkafan, What OS are you on so that I might be able to assist you a little better.

@thedouce69, Putting up an ISO version would be possible albeit pointless, as the file would be much larger.

@Izeball, I doubt there will be anytime soon as someone else stated the Wii scene is in serious decline.  You could always use this NTSC-U one and in whatever loader you're using change the Video Mode setting to "Force PAL50" or "Force PAL60" depending on your specific needs, you could also RegionFrii this image with http://wiki.gbatemp.net/wiki/RegionFrii
